  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, boil a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large bite-sized pieces, then add to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are boiling, add your<strong> chicken breast strips </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!), then reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710160955132-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710160955132-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710160955132-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710160955132-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710160955132-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>diced carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock </strong>and<strong> soft cheese</strong>,<strong> </strong>bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2281-Step-4-x200.jpg",
